ons","grimace-in-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"A noção de torcer a boca na língua Lojban","directory":"pt"},{"slug":["pt","questions","history-of-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"História do Lojban","directory":"pt"},{"slug":["questions","grimace-in-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"The notion of grimace in Lojban language","directory":"questions"},{"slug":["questions","history-of-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"History of Lojban","directory":"questions"},{"slug":["ru","articles","are-verbs-in-lojban-broken"],"hidden":false,"title":"Сломаны ли глаголы в Lojban?","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","articles","complete-lojban-language"],"hidden":false,"title":"📕 Грамматика","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","articles","dialects"],"hidden":false,"title":"Диалекты Ложбана","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","articles","how-to-say-play-in-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"Как сказать \"играть\" на языке Ложбан","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","articles","krulermorna"],"hidden":false,"title":"алфавит krulermorna","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","articles","live_chat"],"hidden":false,"title":"💬 Чат","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","articles","lojban-and-speed-of-thought"],"hidden":false,"title":"Язык Ложбан и скорость мышления","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","articles","sutysisku-picture-dictionary"],"hidden":false,"title":"la sutysisku: иллюстрированный словарь","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","articles","sutysisku_semantic_search"],"hidden":false,"title":"la sutysisku и поиск похожих слов","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","books","!lojban-patterns"],"hidden":true,"title":"🧩 «Алгоритмы и шаблоны на Lojban, Haskell, Rust, JavaScript»","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","books","core-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"📝 Эссе \"Основы Ложбана\"","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","books","learn-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"🎓 Изучаем ложбан","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","books","prostaya-logika"],"hidden":false,"title":"Зачем нужна логика?","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","questions","grimace-in-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"Понятие гримасы в языке Ложбан","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["ru","questions","history-of-lojban"],"hidden":false,"title":"История Ложбана","directory":"ru"},{"slug":["texts","a-terrorist-he-is-watching"],"hidden":false,"title":"A terrorist, he is watching","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","alice-in-wonderland"],"hidden":false,"title":"Alice in Wonderland","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","how-the-enemy-came-to-thlunrana"],"hidden":false,"title":"How the enemy came to Thlunrana","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","in-a-bitter-hour"],"hidden":false,"title":"In A Bitter Hour","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","jokes"],"hidden":false,"title":"Jokes","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","lords-prayer"],"hidden":false,"title":"Lord's prayer","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","navy-seal-copypasta"],"hidden":false,"title":"Navy Seal Copypasta","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","terry-the-tiger-visits-the-big-city"],"hidden":false,"title":"Terry the Tiger Visits the Big City","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","the-bad-beginning"],"hidden":false,"title":"The Bad Beginning","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","the-book"],"hidden":false,"title":"The Book","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","the-girl-from-ipanema"],"hidden":false,"title":"The Girl from Ipanema","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","the-mask"],"hidden":false,"title":"The Mask","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","the-north-wind-and-the-sun"],"hidden":false,"title":"The North Wind and the Sun","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","there-will-come-soft-rains"],"hidden":false,"title":"There Will Come Soft Rains","directory":"texts"},{"slug":["texts","to-kill-a-child"],"hidden":false,"title":"To Kill a Child","directory":"texts"}],"currentLanguage":"articles","post":{"slug":["articles","krulermorna"],"title":"krulermorna alphabet","hidden":false,"content":"<p><strong>la krulermorna</strong> is an alternative orthography that more strictly implements audio-visual isomorphism of Lojban spelling.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Most letters are from the original Latin-based orthography.</li>\n<li>Glides <strong>i</strong> and <strong>u</strong> in front of vowels are considered consonants and thus are expressed via distinct letters:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>i</strong> => <strong>ɩ</strong></li>\n<li><strong>u</strong> => <strong>w</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Diphthongs that act like other \"pure\" vowels are expressed via distinct letters:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>au</strong> => <strong>ǎ</strong></li>\n<li><strong>ai</strong> => <strong>ą</strong></li>\n<li><strong>ei</strong> => <strong>ę</strong></li>\n<li><strong>oi</strong> => <strong>ǫ</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>in other positions <strong>i</strong> and <strong>u</strong> are retained as they are in the original Latin orthography.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"usage\">Usage<a class=\"print:hidden\" aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#usage\"><span class=\"in-heading hash\">#</span></a></h2>\n<p>la krulermorna is used by an algorithm in <a href=\"https://la-lojban.github.io/sutysisku/en/\" title=\"la sutysisku\">la sutysisku</a> app to search for rhymes to Lojban words.</p>\n<p>It can also help understand Lojban morphology.</p>\n<p>Other than that it's mostly an art project.</p>\n<p>The overal number of letters in Lojban alphabet is raised from 26 in the official spelling up to 32 in la krulermorna, which may not be desirable for people using small on-screen keyboards like those on portable devices.</p>\n<h2 id=\"la-vlipa-krulermorna\">la vlipa krulermorna<a class=\"print:hidden\" aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#la-vlipa-krulermorna\"><span class=\"in-heading hash\">#</span></a></h2>\n<figure class=\"wide\">\n\t<img src=\"https://github.com/La-Lojban/suho-pixra-pe-la-jbotcan/blob/master/320px-la_vlipa_krulermorna.png?raw=true\" alt=\"la vlipa krulermorna\">\n\t<figcaption>\n\t.i coi do<br>.i mi ca jai gau djuno fai do<br>lo du'u wi mi ca pilno<br>la krulermorna<br>lo ka ciska dei<br>.i ɩa ky. jai cinri\n\t</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><em>la vlipa krulermorna</em> is a modification of la krulermorna where the letter <strong>ǎ</strong> is replaced with Unicode Character 'LATIN SMALL LETTER AU'. The latter isn't supported in most used fonts and therefore this variant of la krulermorna orthography is less used.</p>\n<h2 id=\"interjections-according-to-krulerske\">Interjections according to krulerske<a class=\"print:hidden\" aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#interjections-according-to-krulerske\"><span class=\"in-heading hash\">#</span></a></h2>\n<p>|          |           |              |        |\n| -------- | --------- | ------------ | ------ |\n| .ǎ       | .ą        | .ę           | .ǫ     |\n| Wish ... | I'm gonna | it should be | ouch! |</p>\n<div class=\"first_col\">\n<p>|     | a               | e                | i                   | o             | u               |\n| --- | --------------- | ---------------- | ------------------- | ------------- | --------------- |\n| .   |                 |                  |                     |               |                 |\n| ɩ   | I believe       | aye! agreed!   | yikes!             | respect       | I love it       |\n| w   | discovery       | What a surprise  | hooray!            | voila!       | oh poor thing   |\n| .a' | I'm listening   | alertness        | oomph! (effort)    | I hope        | hm, I wonder... |\n| .e' | you may         | come on, do it! | do it!             | please, do it | I suggest       |\n| .i' | ok, I accept it | I approve!      | I know that feeling | thanks to it  | familiarity     |\n| .o' | pride           | closeness        | danger!            | patience      | relaxation      |\n| .u' | gain            | what a wonder!  | hahaha!            | courage       | sorry!         |</p>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"alternative-representation\">Alternative representation<a class=\"print:hidden\" aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#alternative-representation\"><span class=\"in-heading hash\">#</span></a></h2>\n<div class=\"first_col\">\n<p>|     | a          | e          | i            | o            | u           | ǎ      | ą      | ę          | ǫ              |\n| --- | ---------- | ---------- | ------------ | ------------ | ----------- | ------ | ------ | ---------- | -------------- |\n| .   |            |            |              |              |             | desire | intent | obligation | complaint/pain |\n| ɩ   | belief     | agreement  | fear         | respect      | love        |        |        |            |                |\n| w   | discovery  | surprise   | happiness    | completion   | pity        |        |        |            |                |\n| .a' | attentive  | alertness  | effort       | hope         | interest    |        |        |            |                |\n| .e' | permission | competence | constraint   | request      | suggestion  |        |        |            |                |\n| .i' | acceptance | approval   | togetherness | appreciation | familiarity |        |        |            |                |\n| .o' | pride      | closeness  | caution      | patience     | relaxation  |        |        |            |                |\n| .u' | gain       | wonder     | amusement    | courage      | repentance  |        |        |            |                |</p>\n</div>","fullPath":"/app/src/md_pages/articles/krulermorna.md","toc":[{"depth":"2","value":"Usage","id":"usage","tagName":"h2"},{"depth":"2","value":"la vlipa krulermorna","id":"la-vlipa-krulermorna","tagName":"h2"},{"depth":"2","value":"Interjections according to krulerske","id":"interjections-according-to-krulerske","tagName":"h2"},{"depth":"2","value":"Alternative representation","id":"alternative-representation","tagName":"h2"}],"imgs":[]}},"__N_SSG":true}